
# Testing the SPEC parser

The SPEC parser is written in SML using ml-antlr and ml-ulex. SPEC can
be compiled with both `MLTON` and `SML/NJ`. Currently ml-ulex has a bug
which makes an ugly hack necessary after grammar regeneration.

## Repository checkout

    $ hg clone ssh://hg@bitbucket.org/mb0/mltk


## Compiling with `MLTON`

- Install `MLTON` see: http://www.mlton.org

    $ cd $CLONE
    $ mlton mltk.mlb
    $ ./mltk examples/x86.spec

## Compiling with SML/NJ

- Install `SML/NJ` see: http://www.smlnj.org

    $ cd $CLONE
    $ rlwrap sml
    - CM.make "mltk.cm";
    - Main.run "examples/x86.spec";

-- h4ppy h4ck1n9
